Emergency services were on Friday afternoon rushing to the scene of an apparent gas leak near the Durban harbour with six people reportedly dead. The &#8220;mass casulty&#8221; incident took place at about midday sources said. According to emergency services who spoke to TMG Digital on condition of anonymity a group of workers were reportedly underground when there was a gas leak. A TMG Digital reporter and photographer were heading to scene. This is a breaking story and will be updated. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share